<paragraph blockId="17.[264,1325,758,1865]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,661,878,904]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Derivation of specific name.</emphasis>
The specific epithet, 
<emphasis box="[915,1010,879,904]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName box="[915,1006,879,904]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Aspasiola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="steineri">steineri</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
is used as a noun in apposition based on the last name of Warren Steiner, who has contributed significantly to our field knowledge of the species richness in 
<taxonomicName box="[776,908,959,985]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
. The 
<collectionCode box="[976,1066,959,985]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">NMNH</collectionCode>
collection, where his collection is deposited, vouchers his many years of efforts and includes the 
<typeStatus box="[1154,1205,999,1025]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
specimen of this new species.
</paragraph>
